      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SUPER SKUNK (5) has some solid form under his belt and proved too classy last time to win by 3.5 lengths at Taree Super Track in a handy 17.98 beating Little Kaos. Well placed and will be tough to beat. PUSH US (8) placed two back then broke his maiden status by 2 lengths (17.86) at Taree Super Track over 300m. Boxed wide here. Yet to win at the journey but has run some good races. Harder here but expected to feature again. RATTLIN' MAGIC (1) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing eighth (23.28) in a Grade 5 at Gosford. Has a strong record out of this box with two wins and a minor placing from five starts. Shapes as one to consider. NOAH'S OWN (2) is right in the mix.",
